source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_SEQ_00<tab>A modest maiden in Kugane is looking for one who is no stranger to adventure.
target: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_SEQ_00<tab>クガネの気弱そうな女は、旅慣れた者を探しているようだ。
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TODO_00<tab>イバラに「不満を表す」をする

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TODO_01<tab>Show Ibara how /angry you are once again.
target: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TODO_01<tab>イバラに再度「不満を表す」をする

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_000<tab>E-Excuse me. Are you an adventurer? You are, aren't you? I wonder, would you not hear me out for a moment? I am in dire need of help.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_000<tab>あ、あの……旅の方ですか？
それなら、少しお話を聞いていただきたいのです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_001<tab>I am on an errand for the master of the estate where I serve. I was sent to the Exchange to purchase an item, and so did. Only, I have just discovered the price I was charged and paid to be well above market value. I returned to demand a refund of the difference, but the shopkeeper would not so much as speak to me.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_001<tab>さきほど、お屋敷の主人に頼まれたものを市で購入したのですが、
言われるままに支払ってしまった金額が、相場よりも高くて……。
店主に抗議しに行ったところ、相手にもされませんでした。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_002<tab>My master is a strict man, and I fear he will take the amount I have cost him out of my pay. Please, I beg you. Would you go and speak with this shopkeep? She must right this wrong.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_002<tab>主人は厳しい方で、このままではお給金が減らされてしまいます。
旅慣れたあなたでしたら、交渉にも長けているのではないかと、
こうしてお話をさせていただきました。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_003<tab>I am far too modest a mouse to show my anger. Would you go and show the shopkeep Ibara how <var 48 F201F4 /var><var 49 F201F5 /var>angry<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var> I am in my stead? No doubt your wrath will serve to retrieve the gil I have been cheated of.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_003<tab>私の代わりに、イバラさんに「不満を表して」いただけませんか？
そして、お金を取り戻していただきたいんです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_004<tab>I am far too modest a mouse to show my anger. Would you go and show the shopkeep Ibara how <var 48 F201F4 /var><var 49 F201F5 /var>angry<var 49 01 /var><var 48 01 /var> I am in my stead? No doubt your wrath will serve to retrieve the gil I have been cheated of.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_004<tab>私の代わりに、イバラさんに「不満を表して」いただけませんか？
そして、お金を取り戻していただきたいんです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_010<tab>You come to my place of business and sling false accusations at me? That fool woman knew full well what I was asking and what she paid. It ain't none of your business besides, wanderer. Now get out of my sight!
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_010<tab>言いがかりかい？
あの女だって、ちゃんと納得して買っていったんだ。
関係ない奴は、とっとと失せな！

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_011<tab>I'm bloody busy here. If you've no mind to spend your gil on my wares, I've no mind to spend my time on you. Now leave.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_011<tab>なんだい？　こっちは忙しいんだ。
客じゃないなら、どっかに行きな。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_020<tab>You're a persistent bugger, ain't ya? Keep it down. There's others about who mean to part with their gil. I'll not suffer you to scare them off.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_020<tab>し、しつこい奴だね。
ほかのカモ……じゃない、客に聞かれたらどうするんだい。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_021<tab>Alright, alright! Calm yourself. It's naught but a paltry sum, anyhow.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_021<tab>わかった、わかった！
どうせ、端金さ。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_022<tab>But I'll not see it to your hand. You could be a thief for all I know or care. Tell the wench to come and claim her coin for herself.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_022<tab>返してやるから取りに来いって、あの女に伝えな。
アンタが盗まないとも、限らないからね。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_023<tab>I'll not see the gil to your hand. You could be a thief for all I know or care. Tell the wench to come and claim her coin for herself.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_IBARA_000_023<tab>返してやるから取りに来いって、あの女に伝えな。
アンタが盗まないとも、限らないからね。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_030<tab>Oh, thank you, thank you, thank you! I will go and claim my coin indeed. That much I can do on my own. The gods are good for sending you to me. Such a kind soul you are!
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_030<tab>ありがとうございます！
取りに行くくらいは、自分でできるようにならないとですね。
あなたが優しい人で、本当によかった。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_031<tab>I confess, you remind me of my own father. He always toils tirelessly for our family, thinking nothing of himself. He came to suffer an injury in his work some days past. Now he is bedridden while he recovers.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_031<tab>なんだか、故郷の父のことを思い出します。
父は、いつも家族のために働いてくれて……。
そのせいで、仕事中に大怪我を負って、今は治療中なんです。

source: TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_032<tab>That is why I am here. I must do what I can to support my family until he is healthy. But I see now it is no easy thing to earn gil in this world. I must grow stronger. No more must I suffer these vile merchants to prey upon me. You have taught me that today, and for that I am grateful. Thank you.
target:
TEXT_STMBDZ117_02667_TIMIDWOMAN02667_000_032<tab>代わりに私が出稼ぎに出てきたのですが、辛くはありません。
家族のためにも、もっと頑張らないと……。
本当に、ありがとうございました。
